data.name: comboBox1.ToolTip
data.value: Set the photometric interpretation tag. Default is MINISBLACK, but if the input image has 3 or 4 bands of Byte type, then RGB will be selected

data.name: OutputTypeListbox.ToolTip
data.value: For the output bands to be of the indicated data type.

data.name: textBox1.ToolTip
data.value: Override the projection for the output file. The srs_def may be any of the usual GDAL/OGR forms, complete WKT, PROJ.4, EPSG:n or a file containing the WKT. For example: EPSG:26918

data.name: TiledCheckbox.ToolTip
data.value: By default stripped TIFF files are created. This option can be used to force creation of tiled TIFF files

data.name: Zlevel.ToolTip
data.value: Set the level of compression when using DEFLATE compression. A value of 9 is best, and 1 is least compression. The default is 6.

data.name: InputfileTextbox.ToolTip
data.value: The source dataset name. It can be either file name, URL of data source or subdataset name for multi-dataset files.

data.name: checkBox5.ToolTip
data.value: Copy all subdatasets of this file to individual output files. Use with formats like HDF or OGDI that have subdatasets.

data.name: compressionListbox.ToolTip
data.value: Set the compression to use. JPEG should generally only be used with Byte data (8 bit per channel).

data.name: chkAddToMap.ToolTip
data.value: Add the resulting raster to the map?

data.name: JpegQuality.ToolTip
data.value: Set the JPEG quality when using JPEG compression. A value of 100 is best quality (least compression), and 1 is worst quality (best compression). The default is 75.

data.name: checkBox3.ToolTip
data.value: Don't be forgiving of mismatches and lost data when translating to the output format.

data.name: CommandTextbox.ToolTip
data.value: The options that will be parsed. You can manually change them and/or add more options.

data.name: OutputfileSelectButton.ToolTip
data.value: Give the name and location of the output raster file.

data.name: checkBox1.ToolTip
data.value: Force the generation of an associated ESRI world file.

data.name: textBox2.ToolTip
data.value: Assign a specified nodata value to output bands. Can be set to none to avoid setting a nodata value to the output file if one exists for the source file.

data.name: checkBox4.ToolTip
data.value: Apply the scale/offset metadata for the bands to convert scaled values to unscaled values. It is also often necessary to reset the output datatype with the -ot switch.
